17/04/2011
ANKARA, Turkey -- A new border crossing between Turkey and Iran opened on Saturday (April 16th) at a ceremony attended by Turkish Foreign Minister Ahmet Davutoglu and Iranian counterpart Ali Akbar Salehi. The Kapikoy-Razi border crossing is expected to boost trade between the neighbours. Davutoglu announced that two more crossings will open soon. (Anadolu news agency, World Bulletin - 16/04/11) 
